Rating: 1
Made this for Christmas Eve dinner for 11 people and almost doubled the recipe. In the end I'm glad I didn't as people were not crazy about it. I thought for sure my husband would love it as corn bread and cilantro are two of his favorite foods. The Fritos seem to give the dish an almost burnt taste and to me, the corn flavor is too strong. I much prefer other stuffing recipes.

Rating: 3
This dish was a huge hit! I was a little worried because my family has a pretty traditional palate but they loved it. We cheated by using store bought corn bread but it still was delicious. Definitely a keeper.

Rating: 4
I try to make a different stuffing each Thanksgiving and after an extensive search I decided to try this one. The sausage and the pecans were an interesting addition. The stuffing was enjoyed by everyone. I did take the advise of adding additional stuffing to mellow it out.

